The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Sept. 22 (PTI): The Centre today announced a bonus of up to Rs 3,500 for its non-gazetted employees.          
	All central government employees in Group C and D and all gazetted employees in Group B not covered by any productivity-linked bonus scheme will get bonus equivalent to 30 days emoluments, the finance ministry said. The scheme will also cover central police, paramilitary and army personnel.                  
	London (PTI): An Indian waiter on a cruise ship docked in Southampton hanged himself after being allegedly caught stealing cash. Goa resident Sumith Gawas, 22, a junior waiter on Arcadia, tried to hide 140 when he was caught emptying a tip box on July 16.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): The Armed Forces Tribunal has allowed a petition which will entitle to enhanced benefits all army majors and officers of equivalent rank in the other services who had retired before 2006. The tribunal has asked the defence ministry to do away with the anomalies in the Sixth Pay Commission within the next three months.                  
	Singapore (PTI): Pakistani grannies should be exempted from visa restrictions imposed by Delhi because of security reasons so that they may visit their relatives in India, an Indian tourist visa forum has been told by tour operators.                  
	Panaji (PTI): The Indian Navy has enhanced its might on the Goa shore by inducting two fast-attack vessels, said public relation officer Commander M.C. Joshi. The water-jet propelled vessels have been indigenously designed and built.
                                                                                                                                              
